## Testing

### Unit Tests

```typescript
import { GitHubAppClient } from "./app";

// Mock @octokit/app
vi.mock("@octokit/app", () => ({
  App: vi.fn().mockImplementation(() => ({
    getInstallationOctokit: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue({
      auth: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue({ token: "ghs_test_token_123" }),
      rest: { /* mock API methods */ },
    }),
  })),
}));

describe("GitHubAppClient", () => {
  let client: GitHubAppClient;

  beforeEach(() => {
    process.env.GITHUB_APP_ID = "12345";
    process.env.GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY = "-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\ntest\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----";
    process.env.GITHUB_APP_WEBHOOK_SECRET = "test-secret";
    client = new GitHubAppClient();
  });

  describe("getInstallationToken", () => {
    it("returns a token from GitHub on first call", async () => {
      const token = await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      expect(token).toBe("ghs_test_token_123");
    });

    it("returns cached token on subsequent calls within TTL", async () => {
      const token1 = await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      const token2 = await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      expect(token1).toBe(token2);
      // Verify getInstallationOctokit was only called once
    });

    it("fetches new token after cache expires", async () => {
      await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      // Advance time past 55 minutes
      vi.advanceTimersByTime(56 * 60 * 1000);
      await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      // Verify getInstallationOctokit was called twice
    });

    it("caches tokens per installation ID", async () => {
      await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      await client.getInstallationToken(99002);
      // Verify two separate API calls were made
    });
  });

  describe("getInstallationOctokit", () => {
    it("returns an Octokit instance", async () => {
      const octokit = await client.getInstallationOctokit(99001);
      expect(octokit).toBeDefined();
      expect(octokit.auth).toBeDefined();
    });
  });

  describe("invalidateToken", () => {
    it("forces a fresh token on next request", async () => {
      await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      client.invalidateToken(99001);
      await client.getInstallationToken(99001);
      // Verify two API calls were made despite being within TTL
    });
  });
});
```

### Key Test Scenarios

| Scenario | Expected Behavior |
|----------|-------------------|
| First token request | Calls GitHub API, caches result, returns token |
| Second request within 55 min | Returns cached token, no API call |
| Request after 55 min | Fetches new token from API |
| Different installation IDs | Separate cache entries, separate API calls |
| `invalidateToken()` then request | Fetches fresh token despite time remaining |
| Constructor with missing env vars | Defers error to first API call (non-null assertion) |

---

## Error Handling

| Error | Cause | Response |
|-------|-------|----------|
| `@octokit/app` auth failure | Invalid App ID or private key | Throws -- caller should catch and log |
| Installation not found | App not installed on repo | 404 from GitHub API -- throws |
| Rate limited | >5000 requests/hour | 403 from GitHub -- caller should retry with backoff |
| Network error | GitHub API unreachable | Throws -- caller should retry |

The `GitHubAppClient` does not handle retries internally. Callers (webhook handler, build system) are responsible for retry logic. If a 401 is received during an API call using a cached token, the caller should call `invalidateToken()` and retry once.
